      <h1>About me</h1>

      <p>I&rsquo;m Niko, a medical doctor turned neuroscientist and image analyst. Since October 2022, I work as a Research Software Engineer at the <a href="https://www.sainsburywellcome.org/web/">Sainsbury Wellcome Centre</a> and <a href="https://www.ucl.ac.uk/gatsby/">Gatsby Computational Neuroscience Unit</a>.</p>
  <p>I completed my PhD at the Functional Imaging Lab</a> of the <a href="https://www.dpz.eu">German Primate Center</a>, where I studied the effects of anesthesia on brain function using neuroimaging techniques, including functional Magnetic Resonance Imaging (fMRI) and in vivo 2‐photon calcium imaging.</p>
  <p>I care about promoting open, collaborative, and reproducible science. In my free time, you will find me dancing to swing music and trying to play the saxophone.</p>


